<subSubSection id="8857AA225C1DCBD75AEFFFD82D7640FA" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0026135AA97CAE1E2A4B9B9F99A8BA84" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65143481585600FEEA9ABF5E16F79003" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<bibRefCitation id="80C9593CB774EF5F349F92F0BAD165A0" author="Cresson, ET Jr" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="165 - 195" title="Studies in the dipterous family Ephydridae. Paper II." volume="55" year="1929">Cresson (1929</bibRefCitation>
: 176) suggested that a male from Vienna, Austria (Mik), was conspecific with this species. Cresson was probably mistaken and may have confused 
<taxonomicName id="4BE6ECFD3E60A086715D562A2006352C" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allotrichoma bezzii" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bezzii">Allotrichoma bezzii</taxonomicName>
with this species. A second Palearctic species, 
<taxonomicName id="F26D9101295BA5A0E0DDF1BC90B8BB2F" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allotrichoma picenum" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picenum">Allotrichoma picenum</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="0E28DB52367A0D94216ABF9FC3F980C7" author="Canzoneri, S" journalOrPublisher="Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali - Lavori" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="43 - 46" title="Osservazioni sul genere Allotrichoma Becker (Diptera, Ephydridae)." volume="15" year="1990">Canzoneri and Rampini (1990</bibRefCitation>
: 44; Italy), is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7BFC2BE8390C5C303C409823841F5F5F" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allotrichoma lasiocercum" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasiocercum">Allotrichoma lasiocercum</taxonomicName>
but has shorter cerci.
</paragraph>
